ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR NHS USE:

1. MEDICAL DATA COMPLIANCE: This software is designed for NHS environments and
   must comply with NHS Digital security standards and GDPR requirements when
   processing healthcare-related whistleblowing reports.

2. ENCRYPTION REQUIREMENTS: All implementations must maintain end-to-end
   encryption for sensitive data. Encryption keys must be managed according
   to NHS Digital cryptographic standards.

3. AUDIT REQUIREMENTS: All deployments must maintain comprehensive audit logs
   as required by NHS governance and regulatory frameworks.

4. DATA RETENTION: Implementations must enforce the 90-day data retention
   policy for submission data while maintaining 7-year retention for audit
   logs as per NHS requirements.

5. SECURITY DISCLOSURE: Security vulnerabilities affecting NHS deployments
   must be reported to NHS Digital security teams in addition to the project
   maintainers.